==English==

===Etymology===
compound word from the Latin ''velox'', ''veloci''&nbsp;&nbsp;swift + ''ped''&nbsp;&nbsp;foot

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: / vɪ' lɒsɪpid /

====Hyphenation====
ve&middot;lo&middot;ci&middot;ped

===Noun===
'''velocipede'''

# Early two-wheeled conveyance upon which one rode astride a wooden frame propelled by means of pushing the feet against the ground c1818. The term then became generic for three and four-wheeled machines driven by foot or hand levers to the rear or front axle. In the late 1860s the bicycle driven by cranks on the front axle was developed in France and provided a brief craze. It was soon after termed a [[boneshaker]] due to its rigid construction.
# Alternative term used to describe the bicycle in general. ''(contemporary usage)''

